Other events shaping our country were the upgrading of both domestic and commercial airports and ports, the building and installation of our new international airport with the largest capital expenditure since independence at $300 million and the remaining $1.3 billion for our “Cruise Port Project” which represents the single largest capital expenditure of our country in the past two decades.

It is imperative for us continue to work with ATTOB and develop strategies to address the challenges and take advantage of the opportunities that exist for our industry, a fact confirmed by the significant growth that our industry has shown over the past decade and recent projections by National Insurance Board for future employment. I would like to commend the efforts of ATTOB for the work and support they have rendered. We certainly look forward to more successful events and experiences as we collectively work, to fast track economic actions and activities to build a sustainable environment in the tourism industry.

8. What advice would you give young people who are interested in making a career in tourism?

I would say to them that this industry that has an exciting and challenging future. Opportunities abound for students to take advantage of foreign exchange programs and other exchange programs prior to completion of their studies.
